quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  70,1,"A beseecher besought the visitation of chastisement,"{1},footnotes:1:1
  70,2,"(a chastisement meant) for the unbelievers, one which none can avert;"
  70,3,"a chastisement from Allah, the Lord of the ascending steps,"{1},footnotes:1:1
  70,4,"by which the angels and the Spirit ascend to Him in one Day the duration of which is fifty thousand years."{1}{2}{3},footnotes:1:1,footnotes:2:2,footnotes:3:3
  70,5,"So, (O Prophet), persevere with gracious perseverance."{1},footnotes:1:1
  70,6,"Verily they think that the chastisement is far off,"
  70,7,"while We think that it is near at hand."{1},footnotes:1:1
  70,8,"It shall befall on a Day whereon the sky will become like molten brass,"{1}{2},footnotes:1:1,footnotes:2:2
  70,9,"and the mountains will become like dyed tufts of wool,"{1},footnotes:1:1
  70,10,"and no bosom friend will enquire about any of his bosom friends"